      • deregister

        public void deregister(java.util.Collection<? extends EidHolder> items)
        Description copied from interface: ItemRegistry
        Deregister items Clients that are dependent on these elements are informed about the de-registration. Note: does not remove the ItemRegistry.DependencyChangeListener, that may have been created when ItemRegistry.lookupDependency(Collection, DependencyChangeListener) has been called. See ItemRegistry.deregisterCallback(DependencyChangeListener) for that case. Items that are not found are silently ignored.
        Specified by:
        deregister in interface ItemRegistry
        Parameters:
        items - items to deregister

      • lookupDependency

        public EidHolderMap<? extends Dto> lookupDependency(java.util.Collection<EID> dependencies,
                                                    ItemRegistry.DependencyChangeListener callbackListener)
        Description copied from interface: ItemRegistry
        Look up specific objects that are created at run time. If the dependencies can be resolved, they are returned directly. The listener is informed when an object on which he depends disappears ( ItemRegistry.DependencyChangeListener.fireEventDependencyDeregistered(Class, EID) callback). If a dependency is unknown, the listener is informed ( ItemRegistry.DependencyChangeListener.fireEventDependencyResolved(Dto) callback) as soon as the object is available.
        Specified by:
        lookupDependency in interface ItemRegistry
        Parameters:
        dependencies - dependencies the requesting object depends on
        callbackListener - the callback interface of the requesting object
        Returns:
        known dependencies
